ENTRY       EC 1.14.13.136              Enzyme
NAME        2-hydroxyisoflavanone synthase;
            CYP93C;
            IFS;
            isoflavonoid synthase
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            With NADH or NADPH as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen into the other donor
SYSNAME     liquiritigenin,NADPH:oxygen oxidoreductase (hydroxylating, aryl migration)
REACTION    (1) liquiritigenin + O2 + NADPH + H+ = 2,4',7-trihydroxyisoflavanone + H2O + NADP+ [RN:R07777];
            (2) (2S)-naringenin + O2 + NADPH + H+ = 2,4',5,7-tetrahydroxyisoflavanone + H2O + NADP+ [RN:R07778]
ALL_REAC    R07777 R07778;
            (other) R07715
SUBSTRATE   liquiritigenin [CPD:C09762];
            O2 [CPD:C00007];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080];
            (2S)-naringenin [CPD:C00509]
PRODUCT     2,4',7-trihydroxyisoflavanone;
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006];
            2,4',5,7-tetrahydroxyisoflavanone
COMMENT     Requires cytochrome P-450. The reaction involves the migration of the 2-phenyl group of the flavanone to the 3-position of the isoflavanone. The 2-hydroxyl group is derived from the oxygen molecule. EC 4.2.1.105, 2-hydroxyisoflavanone dehydratase, acts on the products with loss of water and formation of genistein and daidzein, respectively.
HISTORY     EC 1.14.13.136 created 2011, modified 2013
